<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>my homepage</title>

<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Fredoka:wght@400;600&family=Quicksand:wght@400;500;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

<style>
body {
  margin: 0;
  font-family: 'Quicksand', sans-serif;
  background: #f7d6e6;
  color: #5a2a3a;
}

.header {
  background: #f6f0dc;
  text-align: center;
  padding: 40px 20px;
}

.header h1 {
  font-family: 'Fredoka', sans-serif;
  font-size: 3.5rem;
  margin: 0;
}

.header p {
  margin-top: 10px;
  font-style: italic;
}

.section {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
}

.block {
  padding: 30px;
}

.red {
  background: #e63946;
  color: white;
}

.cream {
  background: #f6f0dc;
}

.pink {
  background: #ffd6e7;
}

.block h2 {
  font-family: 'Fredoka', sans-serif;
  font-size: 2rem;
  margin-top: 0;
}

.block img {
  width: 100%;
  border-radius: 20px;
  margin-top: 15px;
}

.full {
  padding: 40px;
  text-align: center;
}

.sticker {
  background: #ff8fab;
  display: inline-block;
  padding: 8px 15px;
  border-radius: 20px;
  margin-top: 10px;
}

@media(max-width: 800px) {
  .section {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }
}
</style>
</head>

<body>

<div class="header">
  <h1>Daniela's World:)</h1>
  <p>a collection of things i love</p>
</div>

<div class="section">
  <div class="block cream">
    <h2>hiii</h2>
    <p>
      My name is Daniela. I’m a junior and an art major with minors in biology and
      architecture. I work as a tech in the ER, and one day I hope to become a healthcare architect.
      I love the idea of creating spaces that can help people heal, feel safe, and be cared for.
      I have two kids, which are really just my cats, and they are a huge part of my life.
      My favorite color is pink! I wanted my website to
      feel personal and full of the things that matter to me. I’m someone who loves pretty
      details, meaningful memories, and finding beauty in both art and science.
    </p>
    <img src="IMG_6481.jpg" alt="Photo of Daniela">
  </div>

  <div class="block red">
    <h2>biology</h2>
    <p>
      I enjoy biology and learning about life, how it forms, and how even the smallest things we
      can’t see are still so important. I think it’s beautiful that cells and microscopic structures
      can hold so much meaning and be the foundation of life itself. I used to be a biology major,
      but I felt unsatisfied with what I was learning and knew I needed something that connected
      with me more creatively. Even though I changed paths, biology is still something I deeply love
      and feel connected to, because it reminds me how complex, fragile, and amazing life really is.
    </p>
    <img src="IMG_6651.jpeg" alt="Biology microscope image">
  </div>
</div>

<div class="section">
  <div class="block pink">
    <h2>butterflies</h2>
    <p>
      I have a very emotional connection to butterflies. When I first met my boyfriend, we went to
      see the solar eclipse, and we saw so many butterflies that it almost felt unreal, like a dream.
      Ever since then, seeing butterflies makes me feel so much joy. They feel gentle and meaningful
      to me, almost like a small reminder of beautiful moments I never want to forget. I love how
      they connect to both nature and emotion at the same time.
    </p>
    <img src="IMG_7529.jpeg" alt="Butterfly on hand">
  </div>

  <div class="block cream">
    <h2>little memories</h2>
    <p>
      I included this picture because it was my first drink when I turned 21. I’m really into visuals
      and aesthetics, and I love the joy of capturing special moments in a single photo. Sometimes a
      picture can hold an entire feeling, a whole memory, or even a version of who you were in that
      exact second. I like looking back at photos and remembering not just what happened, but how it
      felt. To me, little memories deserve to be kept too.
    </p>
    <img src="IMG_9172.jpeg" alt="First drink at 21">
  </div>
</div>

<div class="section">
  <div class="block red">
    <h2>my cats</h2>
    <p>
      My cats are almost my whole life. I feel instantly happy whenever I’m around them. They were my
      first ever pets, which makes them even more special to me. They’ve become such a big part of my
      everyday life and bring me so much comfort and peace. Being with them makes home feel and more complete. They’re not just pets to me, they really feel like family,
      and I can’t imagine my life without them.
    </p>
    <img src="IMG_7303.jpeg" alt="One of my cats">
  </div>

  <div class="block pink">
    <h2>christmas baby</h2>
    <p>
      My birthday is on Christmas, which has always made it feel a little more magical and personal.
      That day has always been tied to lights, warmth, decorations, and being surrounded by home.
      I included this picture of my cat in the Christmas tree because it feels like such a perfect
      mix of my life and the holiday. It’s funny, sweet, and chaotic in the best way. Being born on
      Christmas makes birthdays feel different, but also really memorable.
    </p>
    <img src="IMG_7379 (1).JPG" alt="Cat in Christmas tree">
  </div>
</div>

<div class="full cream">
  <p>
    all the things i love ♡
  </p>


</body>
</html>
